# Slope — right triangular prism, 1×1×1, centered at origin.
# Geometrically: a unit cube cut diagonally in half with a single
# straight cut. The 90° corner sits along the back-bottom edge.
# The hypotenuse (slope face) runs from the front-bottom edge to
# the back-top edge, so the ramp faces forward-and-up.
#
# Vertex layout:
#   v1 = back-bottom-left   (-, -, -)
#   v2 = back-bottom-right  (+, -, -)
#   v3 = front-bottom-right (+, -, +)
#   v4 = front-bottom-left  (-, -, +)
#   v5 = top-back-left      (-, +, -)
#   v6 = top-back-right     (+, +, -)
#
# Faces: 1 bottom quad + 1 back quad + 1 slope quad + 2 side triangles.
#
# Winding: each face is wound so the right-hand-rule cross product
# of (v1→v2) × (v1→v3) points OUTWARD (away from the prism interior).
# In Unity's left-handed coord system this corresponds to clockwise
# screen-space winding when viewed from outside, which is what
# Unity treats as front-facing — so single-sided rendering works.
# PlacedPrismMat is also set to render double-sided as a safety net.

o Slope

v -0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5  0.5
v -0.5 -0.5  0.5
v -0.5  0.5 -0.5
v  0.5  0.5 -0.5

# Per-face flat normals.
vn  0.0 -1.0  0.0
vn  0.0  0.0 -1.0
vn  0.0  0.7071068  0.7071068
vn -1.0  0.0  0.0
vn  1.0  0.0  0.0

# Unit-square UVs reused across faces; good enough for a flat-coloured
# placeholder material. Replace if you ever apply a textured material.
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 1.0 0.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 0.0 1.0

# Bottom (quad) — normal -Y. Outward-facing winding from below.
f 2/1/1 3/2/1 4/3/1 1/4/1

# Back wall (quad) — normal -Z. Outward-facing winding from behind.
f 5/1/2 6/2/2 2/3/2 1/4/2

# Slope (quad) — normal +Y+Z. Outward-facing winding from the front-top side.
f 3/1/3 6/2/3 5/3/3 4/4/3

# Left side (triangle) — normal -X. Outward-facing winding from the left.
f 4/1/4 5/2/4 1/3/4

# Right side (triangle) — normal +X. Outward-facing winding from the right.
f 6/1/5 3/2/5 2/3/5
